parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank rollover valve can cause fuel to leak underneath the vehicle, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline inside the vehicle
fuel leaking underneath the vehicle near the exhaust pipe
fuel tank needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause sudden loss of engine power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: engine stops while at a red light

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS module can cause the anti-lock brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: module loses power and then errors out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: front brake calipers become discolored and overheated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The heavy noise from the transmission can be a sign of a underlying problem that can lead to transmission failure, causing the vehicle to become stranded or lose power.

A fuel tank rollover valve failure can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, especially when the engine is cold, and fuel sprays from the injectors. This can result in serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline inside and around the vehicle
fuel sprays from injectors when the engine is cold
fuel leaks from the top of the gas tank.
